page.title: 02Southampton Water
page.content: Much of the block is covered by Southampton Water which is an important shipping route.The waterway is tidal with shingle and mud shorelines.There are jetties,public slipways and sailing clubs. There are hourly ferry and hydrofoil services to Cowes on the Isle of Wight.Some of the large cruise liners use Southampton.these include the Cunard vessel Q.E.2. and P&O liners Canberra and Oriana.Locals tell of five liners each tide moving in the main channel but most movement is limited to container ships,a few cruise ships,Isle of Wight ferries and yachts.
